# Post-Task Pipeline (MANDATORY)

After completing ANY code change in this repository, execute these steps:

## Security Quick Check (Shannon)
Review your changes against:
- 🔴 Injection risks (SQL, command, template)
- 🔴 XSS (user input rendered without sanitization)
- 🔴 Auth bypass (missing checks, hardcoded tokens)
- 🔴 Secrets (API keys, passwords in code)
- 🔴 SSRF / path traversal
- 🔴 IDOR (insecure direct object references)

If ANY found → fix immediately before responding.

Full methodology: `COMBINED/security/security-shannon/SHANNON-PRO.md`

## Self-Learning (Hermes)
If you discovered a novel pattern:
→ Create skill: `COMBINED/skills/{domain}/{name}/SKILL.md`
→ Save to supermemory: `mcp supermemory add "<insight>" tags:[domain]`

## Obsidian Vault Auto-Save (⛔ MANDATORY for non-trivial tasks)
```bash
bash obsidian-update.sh \
  --title "<task title>" \
  --content "<what was done, learned, decided>" \
  --tags "<domain>,<type>"
```
Creates: `obsidian_vibe-coder/sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-HHMM-<title>.md`
Script help: `bash obsidian-update.sh --help`

## Quality Report
End your response with:
```
✅ Security: [PASS/FIXED]
✅ Learned:  [NONE / New pattern: (describe)]
✅ Obsidian: [SAVED to sessions/YYYY-MM-DD-title.md / SKIPPED (reason)]
✅ Changed:  [files]
✅ Tests:    [PASS/FAIL/N/A]
```

